    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-29T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-29T08:00:00-05:00" n="36"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/13</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-29T13:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11:10 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>250. Your undated telegram received this morning. I informally requested
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> yesterday that if the
                    good offices of the <pb facs="0334" n="20" xml:id="pg_20"/> United States could
                    at any time or in any possible way be used, please to inform me. He expressed
                    his thanks and said he would do so. I am renewing the same suggestion
                        to-day.<note n="1" xml:id="d36fn1">See the Ambassador’s telegram of July 31,
                        5 p.m., <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_24">p.
                        24</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
